36/* Replace the cgraph node NODE with PREVAILING_NODE in the cgraph, merging
37 all edges and removing the old node. */
38
39static void
40lto_cgraph_replace_node (struct cgraph_node *node,
41 struct cgraph_node *prevailing_node)
42{
43 struct cgraph_edge *e, *next;
44 bool compatible_p;
45
46 if (symtab->dump_file)
47 {
48 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "Replacing cgraph node %s/%i by %s/%i"
49 " for symbol %s\n",
50 node->name (), node->order,
51 prevailing_node->name (),
52 prevailing_node->order,
53 IDENTIFIER_POINTER ((*targetm.asm_out.mangle_assembler_name)
54 (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (node->decl)))));
55 }
56
57 /* Merge node flags. */
58 if (node->force_output)
59 prevailing_node->mark_force_output ();
60 if (node->forced_by_abi)
61 prevailing_node->forced_by_abi = true;
62 if (node->address_taken)
63 {
64 gcc_assert (!prevailing_node->global.inlined_to);
65 prevailing_node->mark_address_taken ();
66 }
67 if (node->definition && prevailing_node->definition
68 && DECL_COMDAT (node->decl) && DECL_COMDAT (prevailing_node->decl))
69 prevailing_node->merged_comdat = true;
70
71 /* Redirect all incoming edges. */
72 compatible_p
73 = types_compatible_p (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (prevailing_node->decl)),
74 TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (node->decl)));
75 for (e = node->callers; e; e = next)
76 {
77 next = e->next_caller;
78 e->redirect_callee (prevailing_node);
79 /* If there is a mismatch between the supposed callee return type and
80 the real one do not attempt to inline this function.
81 ??? We really need a way to match function signatures for ABI
82 compatibility and perform related promotions at inlining time. */
83 if (!compatible_p)
84 {
85 e->inline_failed = CIF_LTO_MISMATCHED_DECLARATIONS;
86 e->call_stmt_cannot_inline_p = 1;
87 }
88 }
89 /* Redirect incomming references. */
90 prevailing_node->clone_referring (node);
91
92 /* Fix instrumentation references. */
93 if (node->instrumented_version)
94 {
95 gcc_assert (node->instrumentation_clone
96 == prevailing_node->instrumentation_clone);
97 node->instrumented_version->instrumented_version = prevailing_node;
98 if (!prevailing_node->instrumented_version)
99 prevailing_node->instrumented_version = node->instrumented_version;
100 /* Need to reset node->instrumented_version to NULL,
101 otherwise node removal code would reset
102 node->instrumented_version->instrumented_version. */
103 node->instrumented_version = NULL;
104 }
105
106 lto_free_function_in_decl_state_for_node (node);
107
108 if (node->decl != prevailing_node->decl)
109 node->release_body ();
110
111 /* Finally remove the replaced node. */
112 node->remove ();
113}

115/* Replace the cgraph node NODE with PREVAILING_NODE in the cgraph, merging
116 all edges and removing the old node. */
117
118static void
119lto_varpool_replace_node (varpool_node *vnode,
120 varpool_node *prevailing_node)
121{
122 gcc_assert (!vnode->definition || prevailing_node->definition);
123 gcc_assert (!vnode->analyzed || prevailing_node->analyzed);
124
125 prevailing_node->clone_referring (vnode);
126 if (vnode->force_output)
127 prevailing_node->force_output = true;
128 if (vnode->forced_by_abi)
129 prevailing_node->forced_by_abi = true;
130
131 /* Be sure we can garbage collect the initializer. */
132 if (DECL_INITIAL (vnode->decl)
133 && vnode->decl != prevailing_node->decl)
134 DECL_INITIAL (vnode->decl) = error_mark_node;
135
136 /* Check and report ODR violations on virtual tables. */
137 if (DECL_VIRTUAL_P (vnode->decl) || DECL_VIRTUAL_P (prevailing_node->decl))
138 compare_virtual_tables (prevailing_node, vnode);
139
140 if (vnode->tls_model != prevailing_node->tls_model)
141 {
142 bool error = false;
143
144 /* Non-TLS and TLS never mix together. Also emulated model is not
145 compatible with anything else. */
146 if (prevailing_node->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_NONE
147 || prevailing_node->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_EMULATED
148 || vnode->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_NONE
149 || vnode->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_EMULATED)
150 error = true;
151 /* Linked is silently supporting transitions
152 GD -> IE, GD -> LE, LD -> LE, IE -> LE, LD -> IE.
153 Do the same transitions and error out on others. */
154 else if ((prevailing_node->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_REAL
155 || prevailing_node->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_LOCAL_DYNAMIC)
156 && (vnode->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_INITIAL_EXEC
157 || vnode->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_LOCAL_EXEC))
158 prevailing_node->tls_model = vnode->tls_model;
159 else if ((vnode->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_REAL
160 || vnode->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_LOCAL_DYNAMIC)
161 && (prevailing_node->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_INITIAL_EXEC
162 || prevailing_node->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_LOCAL_EXEC))
163 ;
164 else if (prevailing_node->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_INITIAL_EXEC
165 && vnode->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_LOCAL_EXEC)
166 prevailing_node->tls_model = vnode->tls_model;
167 else if (vnode->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_INITIAL_EXEC
168 && prevailing_node->tls_model == TLS_MODEL_LOCAL_EXEC)
169 ;
170 else
171 error = true;
172 if (error)
173 {
174 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (vnode->decl),
175 "%qD is defined with tls model %s", vnode->decl, tls_model_names [vnode->tls_model]);
176 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (prevailing_node->decl),
177 "previously defined here as %s",
178 tls_model_names [prevailing_node->tls_model]);
179 }
180 }
181 /* Finally remove the replaced node. */
182 vnode->remove ();
183}
184
185/* Return non-zero if we want to output waring about T1 and T2.
186 Return value is a bitmask of reasons of violation:
187 Bit 0 indicates that types are not compatible.
188 Bit 1 indicates that types are not compatible because of C++ ODR rule.
189 If COMMON_OR_EXTERN is true, do not warn on size mismatches of arrays.
190 Bit 2 indicates that types are not ODR compatible
191
192 The interoperability rules are language specific. At present we do only
193 full checking for C++ ODR rule and for other languages we do basic check
194 that data structures are of same size and TBAA compatible. Our TBAA
195 implementation should be coarse enough so all valid type transitions
196 across different languages are allowed.
197
198 In partiucular we thus allow almost arbitrary type changes with
199 -fno-strict-aliasing which may be tough of as a feature rather than bug
200 as it allows to implement dodgy tricks in the language runtimes.
201
202 Naturally this code can be strenghtened significantly if we could track
203 down the language of origin. */
204
205static int
206warn_type_compatibility_p (tree prevailing_type, tree type,
207 bool common_or_extern)
208{
209 int lev = 0;
210 bool odr_p = odr_or_derived_type_p (prevailing_type)
211 && odr_or_derived_type_p (type);
212
213 if (prevailing_type == type)
214 return 0;
215
216 /* C++ provide a robust way to check for type compatibility via the ODR
217 rule. */
218 if (odr_p && !odr_types_equivalent_p (prevailing_type, type))
219 lev |= 2;
220
221 /* Function types needs special care, because types_compatible_p never
222 thinks prototype is compatible to non-prototype. */
223 if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE || TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
224 {
225 if (TREE_CODE (type) != TREE_CODE (prevailing_type))
226 lev |= 1;
227 lev |= warn_type_compatibility_p (TREE_TYPE (prevailing_type),
228 TREE_TYPE (type), false);
229 if (TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE
230 && TREE_CODE (prevailing_type) == METHOD_TYPE)
231 lev |= warn_type_compatibility_p (TYPE_METHOD_BASETYPE (prevailing_type),
232 TYPE_METHOD_BASETYPE (type), false);
233 if (prototype_p (prevailing_type) && prototype_p (type)
234 && TYPE_ARG_TYPES (prevailing_type) != TYPE_ARG_TYPES (type))
235 {
236 tree parm1, parm2;
237 for (parm1 = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (prevailing_type),
238 parm2 = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (type);
239 parm1 && parm2;
240 parm1 = TREE_CHAIN (parm1),
241 parm2 = TREE_CHAIN (parm2))
242 lev |= warn_type_compatibility_p (TREE_VALUE (parm1),
243 TREE_VALUE (parm2), false);
244 if (parm1 || parm2)
245 lev |= odr_p ? 3 : 1;
246 }
247 if (comp_type_attributes (prevailing_type, type) == 0)
248 lev |= 1;
249 return lev;
250 }
251
252 /* Get complete type. */
253 prevailing_type = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (prevailing_type);
254 type = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type);
255
256 /* We can not use types_compatible_p because we permit some changes
257 across types. For example unsigned size_t and "signed size_t" may be
258 compatible when merging C and Fortran types. */
259 if (COMPLETE_TYPE_P (prevailing_type)
260 && COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type)
261 /* While global declarations are never variadic, we can recurse here
262 for function parameter types. */
263 && TREE_CODE (TYPE_SIZE (type)) == INTEGER_CST
264 && TREE_CODE (TYPE_SIZE (prevailing_type)) == INTEGER_CST
265 && !tree_int_cst_equal (TYPE_SIZE (type), TYPE_SIZE (prevailing_type)))
266 {
267 /* As a special case do not warn about merging
268 int a[];
269 and
270 int a[]={1,2,3};
271 here the first declaration is COMMON or EXTERN
272 and sizeof(a) == sizeof (int). */
273 if (!common_or_extern
274 || TREE_CODE (type) != ARRAY_TYPE
275 || TYPE_SIZE (type) != TYPE_SIZE (TREE_TYPE (type)))
276 lev |= 1;
277 }
278
279 /* Verify TBAA compatibility. Take care of alias set 0 and the fact that
280 we make ptr_type_node to TBAA compatible with every other type. */
281 if (type_with_alias_set_p (type) && type_with_alias_set_p (prevailing_type))
282 {
283 alias_set_type set1 = get_alias_set (type);
284 alias_set_type set2 = get_alias_set (prevailing_type);
285
286 if (set1 && set2 && set1 != set2)
287 {
288 tree t1 = type, t2 = prevailing_type;
289
290 /* Alias sets of arrays with aliased components are the same as alias
291 sets of the inner types. */
292 while (TREE_CODE (t1) == ARRAY_TYPE
293 && !TYPE_NONALIASED_COMPONENT (t1)
294 && TREE_CODE (t2) == ARRAY_TYPE
295 && !TYPE_NONALIASED_COMPONENT (t2))
296 {
297 t1 = TREE_TYPE (t1);
298 t2 = TREE_TYPE (t2);
299 }
300 if ((!POINTER_TYPE_P (t1) || !POINTER_TYPE_P (t2))
301 || (set1 != TYPE_ALIAS_SET (ptr_type_node)
302 && set2 != TYPE_ALIAS_SET (ptr_type_node)))
303 lev |= 5;
304 }
305 }
306
307 return lev;
308}
309
310/* Merge two variable or function symbol table entries PREVAILING and ENTRY.
311 Return false if the symbols are not fully compatible and a diagnostic
312 should be emitted. */
313
314static bool
315lto_symtab_merge (symtab_node *prevailing, symtab_node *entry)
316{
317 tree prevailing_decl = prevailing->decl;
318 tree decl = entry->decl;
319
320 if (prevailing_decl == decl)
321 return true;
322
323 if (TREE_CODE (decl) != TREE_CODE (prevailing_decl))
324 return false;
325
326 /* Merge decl state in both directions, we may still end up using
327 the new decl. */
328 TREE_ADDRESSABLE (prevailing_decl) |= TREE_ADDRESSABLE (decl);
329 TREE_ADDRESSABLE (decl) |= TREE_ADDRESSABLE (prevailing_decl);
330
331 /* The linker may ask us to combine two incompatible symbols.
332 Detect this case and notify the caller of required diagnostics. */
333
334 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
335 {
336 /* Merge decl state in both directions, we may still end up using
337 the new decl. */
338 DECL_POSSIBLY_INLINED (prevailing_decl) |= DECL_POSSIBLY_INLINED (decl);
339 DECL_POSSIBLY_INLINED (decl) |= DECL_POSSIBLY_INLINED (prevailing_decl);
340
341 if (warn_type_compatibility_p (TREE_TYPE (prevailing_decl),
342 TREE_TYPE (decl),
343 DECL_COMMON (decl)
344 || DECL_EXTERNAL (decl)))
345 return false;
346
347 return true;
348 }
349
350 if (warn_type_compatibility_p (TREE_TYPE (prevailing_decl),
351 TREE_TYPE (decl),
352 DECL_COMMON (decl) || DECL_EXTERNAL (decl)))
353 return false;
354
355 /* There is no point in comparing too many details of the decls here.
356 The type compatibility checks or the completing of types has properly
357 dealt with most issues. */
358
359 /* The following should all not invoke fatal errors as in non-LTO
360 mode the linker wouldn't complain either. Just emit warnings. */
361
362 /* Report a warning if user-specified alignments do not match. */
363 if ((DECL_USER_ALIGN (prevailing_decl) && DECL_USER_ALIGN (decl))
364 && DECL_ALIGN (prevailing_decl) < DECL_ALIGN (decl))
365 return false;
366
367 if (DECL_SIZE (decl) && DECL_SIZE (prevailing_decl)
368 && !tree_int_cst_equal (DECL_SIZE (decl), DECL_SIZE (prevailing_decl)))
369 {
370 if (!DECL_COMMON (decl) && !DECL_EXTERNAL (decl))
371 return false;
372
373 tree type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
374
375 /* For record type, check for array at the end of the structure. */
376 if (TREE_CODE (type) == RECORD_TYPE)
377 {
378 tree field = TYPE_FIELDS (type);
379 while (DECL_CHAIN (field) != NULL_TREE)
380 field = DECL_CHAIN (field);
381
382 return TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (field)) == ARRAY_TYPE;
383 }
384 /* As a special case do not warn about merging
385 int a[];
386 and
387 int a[]={1,2,3};
388 here the first declaration is COMMON
389 and sizeof(a) == sizeof (int). */
390 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
391 return (TYPE_SIZE (decl) == TYPE_SIZE (TREE_TYPE (type)));
392 }
393
394 return true;
395}
396
397/* Return true if the symtab entry E can be replaced by another symtab
398 entry. */
399
400static bool
401lto_symtab_resolve_replaceable_p (symtab_node *e)
402{
403 if (DECL_EXTERNAL (e->decl)
404 || DECL_COMDAT (e->decl)
405 || DECL_ONE_ONLY (e->decl)
406 || DECL_WEAK (e->decl))
407 return true;
408
409 if (TREE_CODE (e->decl) == VAR_DECL)
410 return (DECL_COMMON (e->decl)
411 || (!flag_no_common && !DECL_INITIAL (e->decl)));
412
413 return false;
414}
415
416/* Return true, if the symbol E should be resolved by lto-symtab.
417 Those are all external symbols and all real symbols that are not static (we
418 handle renaming of static later in partitioning). */
419
420static bool
421lto_symtab_symbol_p (symtab_node *e)
422{
423 if (!TREE_PUBLIC (e->decl) && !DECL_EXTERNAL (e->decl))
424 return false;
425 return e->real_symbol_p ();
426}
427
428/* Return true if the symtab entry E can be the prevailing one. */
429
430static bool
431lto_symtab_resolve_can_prevail_p (symtab_node *e)
432{
433 if (!lto_symtab_symbol_p (e))
434 return false;
435
436 /* The C++ frontend ends up neither setting TREE_STATIC nor
437 DECL_EXTERNAL on virtual methods but only TREE_PUBLIC.
438 So do not reject !TREE_STATIC here but only DECL_EXTERNAL. */
439 if (DECL_EXTERNAL (e->decl))
440 return false;
441
442 return e->definition;
443}
444
445/* Resolve the symbol with the candidates in the chain *SLOT and store
446 their resolutions. */
447
448static symtab_node *
449lto_symtab_resolve_symbols (symtab_node *first)
450{
451 symtab_node *e;
452 symtab_node *prevailing = NULL;
453
454 /* Always set e->node so that edges are updated to reflect decl merging. */
455 for (e = first; e; e = e->next_sharing_asm_name)
456 if (lto_symtab_symbol_p (e)
457 && (e->resolution == LDPR_PREVAILING_DEF_IRONLY
458 || e->resolution == LDPR_PREVAILING_DEF_IRONLY_EXP
459 || e->resolution == LDPR_PREVAILING_DEF))
460 {
461 prevailing = e;
462 break;
463 }
464
465 /* If the chain is already resolved there is nothing else to do. */
466 if (prevailing)
467 {
468 /* Assert it's the only one.
469 GCC should silence multiple PREVAILING_DEF_IRONLY defs error
470 on COMMON symbols since it isn't error.
471 See: https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=23079. */
472 for (e = prevailing->next_sharing_asm_name; e; e = e->next_sharing_asm_name)
473 if (lto_symtab_symbol_p (e)
474 && !DECL_COMMON (prevailing->decl)
475 && !DECL_COMMON (e->decl)
476 && (e->resolution == LDPR_PREVAILING_DEF_IRONLY
477 || e->resolution == LDPR_PREVAILING_DEF_IRONLY_EXP
478 || e->resolution == LDPR_PREVAILING_DEF))
479 fatal_error (input_location, "multiple prevailing defs for %qE",
480 DECL_NAME (prevailing->decl));
481 return prevailing;
482 }
483
484 /* Find the single non-replaceable prevailing symbol and
485 diagnose ODR violations. */
486 for (e = first; e; e = e->next_sharing_asm_name)
487 {
488 if (!lto_symtab_resolve_can_prevail_p (e))
489 continue;
490
491 /* If we have a non-replaceable definition it prevails. */
492 if (!lto_symtab_resolve_replaceable_p (e))
493 {
494 if (prevailing)
495 {
496 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (e->decl),
497 "%qD has already been defined", e->decl);
498 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (prevailing->decl),
499 "previously defined here");
500 }
501 prevailing = e;
502 }
503 }
504 if (prevailing)
505 return prevailing;
506
507 /* Do a second round choosing one from the replaceable prevailing decls. */
508 for (e = first; e; e = e->next_sharing_asm_name)
509 {
510 if (!lto_symtab_resolve_can_prevail_p (e))
511 continue;
512
513 /* Choose the first function that can prevail as prevailing. */
514 if (TREE_CODE (e->decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
515 {
516 prevailing = e;
517 break;
518 }
519
520 /* From variables that can prevail choose the largest one. */
521 if (!prevailing
522 || tree_int_cst_lt (DECL_SIZE (prevailing->decl),
523 DECL_SIZE (e->decl))
524 /* When variables are equivalent try to chose one that has useful
525 DECL_INITIAL. This makes sense for keyed vtables that are
526 DECL_EXTERNAL but initialized. In units that do not need them
527 we replace the initializer by error_mark_node to conserve
528 memory.
529
530 We know that the vtable is keyed outside the LTO unit - otherwise
531 the keyed instance would prevail. We still can preserve useful
532 info in the initializer. */
533 || (DECL_SIZE (prevailing->decl) == DECL_SIZE (e->decl)
534 && (DECL_INITIAL (e->decl)
535 && DECL_INITIAL (e->decl) != error_mark_node)
536 && (!DECL_INITIAL (prevailing->decl)
537 || DECL_INITIAL (prevailing->decl) == error_mark_node)))
538 prevailing = e;
539 }
540
541 return prevailing;
542}
543
544/* Decide if it is OK to merge DECL into PREVAILING.
545 Because we wrap most of uses of declarations in MEM_REF, we can tolerate
546 some differences but other code may inspect directly the DECL. */
547
548static bool
549lto_symtab_merge_p (tree prevailing, tree decl)
550{
551 if (TREE_CODE (prevailing) != TREE_CODE (decl))
552 {
553 if (symtab->dump_file)
554 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "Not merging decls; "
555 "TREE_CODE mismatch\n");
556 return false;
557 }
558 gcc_checking_assert (TREE_CHAIN (prevailing) == TREE_CHAIN (decl));
559
560 if (TREE_CODE (prevailing) == FUNCTION_DECL)
561 {
562 if (DECL_BUILT_IN (prevailing) != DECL_BUILT_IN (decl))
563 {
564 if (symtab->dump_file)
565 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "Not merging decls; "
566 "DECL_BUILT_IN mismatch\n");
567 return false;
568 }
569 if (DECL_BUILT_IN (prevailing)
570 && (DECL_BUILT_IN_CLASS (prevailing) != DECL_BUILT_IN_CLASS (decl)
571 || DECL_FUNCTION_CODE (prevailing) != DECL_FUNCTION_CODE (decl)))
572 {
573 if (symtab->dump_file)
574 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "Not merging decls; "
575 "DECL_BUILT_IN_CLASS or CODE mismatch\n");
576 return false;
577 }
578 }
579
580 /* FIXME: after MPX is removed, use flags_from_decl_or_type
581 function instead. PR lto/85248. */
582 if (DECL_ATTRIBUTES (prevailing) != DECL_ATTRIBUTES (decl))
583 {
584 tree prev_attr = lookup_attribute ("error", DECL_ATTRIBUTES (prevailing));
585 tree attr = lookup_attribute ("error", DECL_ATTRIBUTES (decl));
586 if ((prev_attr == NULL) != (attr == NULL)
587 || (prev_attr
588 && TREE_VALUE (TREE_VALUE (prev_attr))
589 != TREE_VALUE (TREE_VALUE (attr))))
590 {
591 if (symtab->dump_file)
592 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "Not merging decls; "
593 "error attribute mismatch\n");
594 return false;
595 }
596
597 prev_attr = lookup_attribute ("warning", DECL_ATTRIBUTES (prevailing));
598 attr = lookup_attribute ("warning", DECL_ATTRIBUTES (decl));
599 if ((prev_attr == NULL) != (attr == NULL)
600 || (prev_attr
601 && TREE_VALUE (TREE_VALUE (prev_attr))
602 != TREE_VALUE (TREE_VALUE (attr))))
603 {
604 if (symtab->dump_file)
605 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "Not merging decls; "
606 "warning attribute mismatch\n");
607 return false;
608 }
609
610 prev_attr = lookup_attribute ("noreturn", DECL_ATTRIBUTES (prevailing));
611 attr = lookup_attribute ("noreturn", DECL_ATTRIBUTES (decl));
612 if ((prev_attr == NULL) != (attr == NULL))
613 {
614 if (symtab->dump_file)
615 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "Not merging decls; "
616 "noreturn attribute mismatch\n");
617 return false;
618 }
619 }
620 return true;
621}
622
623/* Merge all decls in the symbol table chain to the prevailing decl and
624 issue diagnostics about type mismatches. If DIAGNOSED_P is true
625 do not issue further diagnostics.*/
626
627static void
628lto_symtab_merge_decls_2 (symtab_node *first, bool diagnosed_p)
629{
630 symtab_node *prevailing;
631 symtab_node *e;
632 vec<tree> mismatches = vNULL;
633 unsigned i;
634 tree decl;
635 bool tbaa_p = false;
636
637 /* Nothing to do for a single entry. */
638 prevailing = first;
639 if (!prevailing->next_sharing_asm_name)
640 return;
641
642 /* Try to merge each entry with the prevailing one. */
643 symtab_node *last_prevailing = prevailing, *next;
644 for (e = prevailing->next_sharing_asm_name; e; e = next)
645 {
646 next = e->next_sharing_asm_name;
647
648 /* Skip non-LTO symbols and symbols whose declaration we already
649 visited. */
650 if (lto_symtab_prevailing_decl (e->decl) != e->decl
651 || !lto_symtab_symbol_p (e)
652 || e->decl == prevailing->decl)
653 continue;
654
655 if (!lto_symtab_merge (prevailing, e)
656 && !diagnosed_p
657 && !DECL_ARTIFICIAL (e->decl))
658 mismatches.safe_push (e->decl);
659
660 symtab_node *this_prevailing;
661 for (this_prevailing = prevailing; ;
662 this_prevailing = this_prevailing->next_sharing_asm_name)
663 {
664 if (this_prevailing->decl != e->decl
665 && lto_symtab_merge_p (this_prevailing->decl, e->decl))
666 break;
667 if (this_prevailing == last_prevailing)
668 {
669 this_prevailing = NULL;
670 break;
671 }
672 }
673
674 if (this_prevailing)
675 lto_symtab_prevail_decl (this_prevailing->decl, e->decl);
676 /* Maintain LRU list: relink the new prevaililng symbol
677 just after previaling node in the chain and update last_prevailing.
678 Since the number of possible declarations of a given symbol is
679 small, this should be faster than building a hash. */
680 else if (e == prevailing->next_sharing_asm_name)
681 last_prevailing = e;
682 else
683 {
684 if (e->next_sharing_asm_name)
685 e->next_sharing_asm_name->previous_sharing_asm_name
686 = e->previous_sharing_asm_name;
687 e->previous_sharing_asm_name->next_sharing_asm_name
688 = e->next_sharing_asm_name;
689 e->previous_sharing_asm_name = prevailing;
690 e->next_sharing_asm_name = prevailing->next_sharing_asm_name;
691 prevailing->next_sharing_asm_name->previous_sharing_asm_name = e;
692 prevailing->next_sharing_asm_name = e;
693 if (last_prevailing == prevailing)
694 last_prevailing = e;
695 }
696 }
697 if (mismatches.is_empty ())
698 return;
699
700 /* Diagnose all mismatched re-declarations. */
701 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (mismatches, i, decl)
702 {
703 /* Do not diagnose two built-in declarations, there is no useful
704 location in that case. It also happens for AVR if two built-ins
705 use the same asm name because their libgcc assembler code is the
706 same, see PR78562. */
707 if (DECL_IS_BUILTIN (prevailing->decl)
708 && DECL_IS_BUILTIN (decl))
709 continue;
710
711 int level = warn_type_compatibility_p (TREE_TYPE (prevailing->decl),
712 TREE_TYPE (decl),
713 DECL_COMDAT (decl));
714 if (level)
715 {
716 bool diag = false;
717 if (level & 2)
718 diag = warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
719 OPT_Wodr,
720 "%qD violates the C++ One Definition Rule ",
721 decl);
722 if (!diag && (level & 1))
723 diag = warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
724 OPT_Wlto_type_mismatch,
725 "type of %qD does not match original "
726 "declaration", decl);
727 if (diag)
728 {
729 warn_types_mismatch (TREE_TYPE (prevailing->decl),
730 TREE_TYPE (decl),
731 DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (prevailing->decl),
732 DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl));
733 if ((level & 4)
734 && !TREE_READONLY (prevailing->decl))
735 tbaa_p = true;
736 }
737 diagnosed_p |= diag;
738 }
739 else if ((DECL_USER_ALIGN (prevailing->decl)
740 && DECL_USER_ALIGN (decl))
741 && DECL_ALIGN (prevailing->decl) < DECL_ALIGN (decl))
742 {
743 diagnosed_p |= warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
744 OPT_Wlto_type_mismatch,
745 "alignment of %qD is bigger than "
746 "original declaration", decl);
747 }
748 else
749 diagnosed_p |= warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
750 OPT_Wlto_type_mismatch,
751 "size of %qD differ from the size of "
752 "original declaration", decl);
753 }
754 if (diagnosed_p)
755 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (prevailing->decl),
756 "%qD was previously declared here", prevailing->decl);
757 if (tbaa_p)
758 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (prevailing->decl),
759 "code may be misoptimized unless "
760 "-fno-strict-aliasing is used");
761
762 mismatches.release ();
763}
764
765/* Helper to process the decl chain for the symbol table entry *SLOT. */
766
767static void
768lto_symtab_merge_decls_1 (symtab_node *first)
769{
770 symtab_node *e;
771 symtab_node *prevailing;
772 bool diagnosed_p = false;
773
774 if (symtab->dump_file)
775 {
776 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "Merging nodes for %s. Candidates:\n",
777 first->asm_name ());
778 for (e = first; e; e = e->next_sharing_asm_name)
779 if (TREE_PUBLIC (e->decl))
780 e->dump (symtab->dump_file);
781 }
782
783 /* Compute the symbol resolutions. This is a no-op when using the
784 linker plugin and resolution was decided by the linker. */
785 prevailing = lto_symtab_resolve_symbols (first);
786
787 /* If there's not a prevailing symbol yet it's an external reference.
788 Happens a lot during ltrans. Choose the first symbol with a
789 cgraph or a varpool node. */
790 if (!prevailing)
791 {
792 for (prevailing = first;
793 prevailing; prevailing = prevailing->next_sharing_asm_name)
794 if (lto_symtab_symbol_p (prevailing))
795 break;
796 if (!prevailing)
797 return;
798 /* For variables chose with a priority variant with vnode
799 attached (i.e. from unit where external declaration of
800 variable is actually used).
801 When there are multiple variants, chose one with size.
802 This is needed for C++ typeinfos, for example in
803 lto/20081204-1 there are typeifos in both units, just
804 one of them do have size. */
805 if (TREE_CODE (prevailing->decl) == VAR_DECL)
806 {
807 for (e = prevailing->next_sharing_asm_name;
808 e; e = e->next_sharing_asm_name)
809 if (!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (prevailing->decl))
810 && COMPLETE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (e->decl))
811 && lto_symtab_symbol_p (e))
812 prevailing = e;
813 }
814 /* For functions prefer the non-builtin if one is available. */
815 else if (TREE_CODE (prevailing->decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
816 {
817 for (e = first; e; e = e->next_sharing_asm_name)
818 if (TREE_CODE (e->decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
819 && !DECL_BUILT_IN (e->decl)
820 && lto_symtab_symbol_p (e))
821 {
822 prevailing = e;
823 break;
824 }
825 }
826 }
827
828 symtab->symtab_prevail_in_asm_name_hash (prevailing);
829
830 /* Diagnose mismatched objects. */
831 for (e = prevailing->next_sharing_asm_name;
832 e; e = e->next_sharing_asm_name)
833 {
834 if (TREE_CODE (prevailing->decl)
835 == TREE_CODE (e->decl))
836 continue;
837 if (!lto_symtab_symbol_p (e))
838 continue;
839
840 switch (TREE_CODE (prevailing->decl))
841 {
842 case VAR_DECL:
843 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (e->decl) == FUNCTION_DECL);
844 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (e->decl),
845 "variable %qD redeclared as function",
846 prevailing->decl);
847 break;
848
849 case FUNCTION_DECL:
850 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (e->decl) == VAR_DECL);
851 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (e->decl),
852 "function %qD redeclared as variable",
853 prevailing->decl);
854 break;
855
856 default:
857 gcc_unreachable ();
858 }
859
860 diagnosed_p = true;
861 }
862 if (diagnosed_p)
863 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (prevailing->decl),
864 "previously declared here");
865
866 /* Merge the chain to the single prevailing decl and diagnose
867 mismatches. */
868 lto_symtab_merge_decls_2 (prevailing, diagnosed_p);
869
870 if (symtab->dump_file)
871 {
872 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "After resolution:\n");
873 for (e = prevailing; e; e = e->next_sharing_asm_name)
874 e->dump (symtab->dump_file);
875 }
876}
877
878/* Resolve and merge all symbol table chains to a prevailing decl. */
879
880void
881lto_symtab_merge_decls (void)
882{
883 symtab_node *node;
884
885 /* Populate assembler name hash. */
886 symtab->symtab_initialize_asm_name_hash ();
887
888 FOR_EACH_SYMBOL (node)
889 if (!node->previous_sharing_asm_name
890 && node->next_sharing_asm_name)
891 lto_symtab_merge_decls_1 (node);
892}
893
894/* Helper to process the decl chain for the symbol table entry *SLOT. */
895
896static void
897lto_symtab_merge_symbols_1 (symtab_node *prevailing)
898{
899 symtab_node *e;
900 symtab_node *next;
901
902 prevailing->decl->decl_with_vis.symtab_node = prevailing;
903
904 /* Replace the cgraph node of each entry with the prevailing one. */
905 for (e = prevailing->next_sharing_asm_name; e;
906 e = next)
907 {
908 next = e->next_sharing_asm_name;
909
910 if (!lto_symtab_symbol_p (e))
911 continue;
912 cgraph_node *ce = dyn_cast <cgraph_node *> (e);
913 symtab_node *to = symtab_node::get (lto_symtab_prevailing_decl (e->decl));
914
915 /* No matter how we are going to deal with resolution, we will ultimately
916 use prevailing definition. */
917 if (ce)
918 ipa_merge_profiles (dyn_cast<cgraph_node *> (prevailing),
919 dyn_cast<cgraph_node *> (e));
920
921 /* If we decided to replace the node by TO, do it. */
922 if (e != to)
923 {
924 if (ce)
925 lto_cgraph_replace_node (ce, dyn_cast<cgraph_node *> (to));
926 else if (varpool_node *ve = dyn_cast <varpool_node *> (e))
927 lto_varpool_replace_node (ve, dyn_cast<varpool_node *> (to));
928 }
929 /* Watch out for duplicated symbols for a given declaration. */
930 else if (!e->transparent_alias
931 || !e->definition || e->get_alias_target () != to)
932 {
933 /* We got a new declaration we do not want to merge. In this case
934 get rid of the existing definition and create a transparent
935 alias. */
936 if (ce)
937 {
938 lto_free_function_in_decl_state_for_node (ce);
939 if (!ce->weakref)
940 ce->release_body ();
941 ce->reset ();
942 symtab->call_cgraph_removal_hooks (ce);
943 }
944 else
945 {
946 DECL_INITIAL (e->decl) = error_mark_node;
947 if (e->lto_file_data)
948 {
949 lto_free_function_in_decl_state_for_node (e);
950 e->lto_file_data = NULL;
951 }
952 symtab->call_varpool_removal_hooks (dyn_cast<varpool_node *> (e));
953 }
954 e->remove_all_references ();
955 e->analyzed = e->body_removed = false;
956 e->resolve_alias (prevailing, true);
957 gcc_assert (e != prevailing);
958 }
959 }
960
961 return;
962}
963
964/* Merge cgraph nodes according to the symbol merging done by
965 lto_symtab_merge_decls. */
966
967void
968lto_symtab_merge_symbols (void)
969{
970 symtab_node *node;
971
972 if (!flag_ltrans)
973 {
974 symtab->symtab_initialize_asm_name_hash ();
975
976 /* Do the actual merging.
977 At this point we invalidate hash translating decls into symtab nodes
978 because after removing one of duplicate decls the hash is not correcly
979 updated to the ohter dupliate. */
980 FOR_EACH_SYMBOL (node)
981 if (lto_symtab_symbol_p (node)
982 && node->next_sharing_asm_name
983 && !node->previous_sharing_asm_name)
984 lto_symtab_merge_symbols_1 (node);
985
986 /* Resolve weakref aliases whose target are now in the compilation unit.
987 also re-populate the hash translating decls into symtab nodes*/
988 FOR_EACH_SYMBOL (node)
989 {
990 cgraph_node *cnode, *cnode2;
991 varpool_node *vnode;
992 symtab_node *node2;
993
994 if (!node->analyzed && node->alias_target)
995 {
996 symtab_node *tgt = symtab_node::get_for_asmname (node->alias_target);
997 gcc_assert (node->weakref);
998 if (tgt)
999 node->resolve_alias (tgt, true);
1000 }
1001
1002 if (!(cnode = dyn_cast <cgraph_node *> (node))
1003 || !cnode->clone_of
1004 || cnode->clone_of->decl != cnode->decl)
1005 {
1006 /* Builtins are not merged via decl merging. It is however
1007 possible that tree merging unified the declaration. We
1008 do not want duplicate entries in symbol table. */
1009 if (cnode && DECL_BUILT_IN (node->decl)
1010 && (cnode2 = cgraph_node::get (node->decl))
1011 && cnode2 != cnode)
1012 lto_cgraph_replace_node (cnode2, cnode);
1013
1014 /* The user defined assembler variables are also not unified by their
1015 symbol name (since it is irrelevant), but we need to unify symbol
1016 nodes if tree merging occurred. */
1017 if ((vnode = dyn_cast <varpool_node *> (node))
1018 && DECL_HARD_REGISTER (vnode->decl)
1019 && (node2 = symtab_node::get (vnode->decl))
1020 && node2 != node)
1021 lto_varpool_replace_node (dyn_cast <varpool_node *> (node2),
1022 vnode);
1023
1024
1025 /* Abstract functions may have duplicated cgraph nodes attached;
1026 remove them. */
1027 else if (cnode && DECL_ABSTRACT_P (cnode->decl)
1028 && (cnode2 = cgraph_node::get (node->decl))
1029 && cnode2 != cnode)
1030 cnode2->remove ();
1031
1032 node->decl->decl_with_vis.symtab_node = node;
1033 }
1034 }
1035 }
1036}
1037
1038/* Virtual tables may matter for code generation even if they are not
1039 directly refernced by the code because they may be used for devirtualizaiton.
1040 For this reason it is important to merge even virtual tables that have no
1041 associated symbol table entries. Without doing so we lose optimization
1042 oppurtunities by losing track of the vtable constructor.
1043 FIXME: we probably ought to introduce explicit symbol table entries for
1044 those before streaming. */
1045
1046tree
1047lto_symtab_prevailing_virtual_decl (tree decl)
1048{
1049 if (DECL_ABSTRACT_P (decl))
1050 return decl;
1051 gcc_checking_assert (!type_in_anonymous_namespace_p (DECL_CONTEXT (decl))
1052 && DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME_SET_P (decl));
1053
1054 symtab_node *n = symtab_node::get_for_asmname
1055 (DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (decl));
1056 while (n && ((!DECL_EXTERNAL (n->decl) && !TREE_PUBLIC (n->decl))
1057 || !DECL_VIRTUAL_P (n->decl)))
1058 n = n->next_sharing_asm_name;
1059 if (n)
1060 {
1061 /* Merge decl state in both directions, we may still end up using
1062 the other decl. */
1063 TREE_ADDRESSABLE (n->decl) |= TREE_ADDRESSABLE (decl);
1064 TREE_ADDRESSABLE (decl) |= TREE_ADDRESSABLE (n->decl);
1065
1066 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
1067 {
1068 /* Merge decl state in both directions, we may still end up using
1069 the other decl. */
1070 DECL_POSSIBLY_INLINED (n->decl) |= DECL_POSSIBLY_INLINED (decl);
1071 DECL_POSSIBLY_INLINED (decl) |= DECL_POSSIBLY_INLINED (n->decl);
1072 }
1073 lto_symtab_prevail_decl (n->decl, decl);
1074 decl = n->decl;
1075 }
1076 else
1077 symtab_node::get_create (decl);
1078
1079 return decl;
1080}
